# bigocheck

> **The only zero-dependency, CLI-first Big-O complexity checker for Python**

Empirical complexity regression checker: run a target function across input sizes, measure runtimes, and fit against common complexity classes. Ships as both a library and CLI.

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Python 3.9+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![Zero Dependencies](https://img.shields.io/badge/dependencies-zero-green.svg)]()
[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/bigocheck)](https://pypi.org/project/bigocheck/)
[![Downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/bigocheck)](https://pypi.org/project/bigocheck/)
[![Author: gadwant](https://img.shields.io/badge/author-gadwant-purple.svg)](https://github.com/adwantg)

---

## üéØ Features at a Glance

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **üßÆ Time Complexity** | Fits to 9 classes: O(1), O(log n), O(‚àön), O(n), O(n log n), O(n¬≤), O(n¬≥), O(2‚Åø), O(n!) |
| **üìê Space Complexity** | Classifies memory usage to complexity classes |
| **üìè Polynomial Fitting** | Detect O(n^k) for arbitrary k (e.g., O(n^2.34)) |
| **üîÄ Git Commit Tracking** | Track complexity across commits, binary search for regression |
| **‚ö†Ô∏è Instability Detection** | Detect noisy/unreliable benchmark results |
| **üè∑Ô∏è Badge Generation** | SVG badges for READMEs (color-coded by complexity) |
| **üìì Jupyter Integration** | Rich HTML display in notebooks |
| **üì§ CSV/JSON Export** | Export results to CSV, JSON, markdown |
| **üö® Threshold Alerts** | Alert when complexity exceeds threshold (CI/CD) |
| **üìñ Complexity Explanations** | Human-readable explanations of what O(n log n) means |
| **üìè Input Size Recommendations** | Smart input size suggestions for better benchmarks |
| **üèÜ Multi-Algorithm Comparison** | Compare N algorithms at once with rankings |
| **üìê Bounds Checking** | Assert O(log n) ‚â§ f ‚â§ O(n¬≤) ranges |
| **‚öôÔ∏è Benchmark Profiles** | Presets: fast, balanced, accurate, thorough |
| **üìù Auto Documentation** | Auto-generate docstrings with complexity info |
| **üìä Statistical Significance** | P-values to validate complexity classification |
| **üîÑ Regression Detection** | CLI: `bigocheck regression --baseline file.json` |
| **üìâ Best/Worst/Avg Cases** | Analyze with sorted, reversed, and random inputs |
| **‚ö° Async Support** | Benchmark `async def` functions |
| **üìä Amortized Analysis** | Track complexity over sequences of operations |
| **üöÄ Parallel Benchmarking** | Run sizes in parallel for faster results |
| **üìë HTML Reports** | Generate beautiful HTML reports with SVG charts |
| **üíª Interactive REPL** | CLI: `bigocheck repl` for quick analysis |
| **‚úÖ Complexity Assertions** | `@assert_complexity("O(n)")` decorator |
| **üîç Bounds Verification** | `verify_bounds()` to check expected complexity |
| **üìä Confidence Scoring** | Know how reliable your results are |
| **üîÄ A/B Comparison** | Compare two implementations head-to-head |
| **üìÑ Report Generation** | Generate markdown reports automatically |
| **üîß pytest Plugin** | Integration with pytest for testing |
| **üìà Plotting** | Optional matplotlib visualization |
| **üíæ Memory Profiling** | Track peak memory usage with `--memory` flag |
| **üöÄ Auto Size Selection** | Automatically choose optimal input sizes |
| **üì¶ Zero Dependencies** | Pure standard library, no numpy required |
| **üíª CLI-First** | Full command-line interface |
| **‚öôÔ∏è GitHub Actions** | Pre-built CI workflow template |

